<doc id="265186" wikidata="Q940704" url="?curid=265186" title="Kosovo (disambiguation)">
<text>[[Kosovo]], officially the Republic of Kosovo, is a country in Southeast Europe with partial diplomatic recognition.

Kosovo may also refer to:
==Places==
===Entities on the same territory===
*Kosovo and Metohija, an autonomous province that Serbia claims to still have under its sovereignty, and the name of autonomous entitites 1945-1968
*SAP Kosovo, an autonomous province in the Socialist Republic of Serbia 1968-1990
*Kosovo District, an administrative district claimed by Serbia in central Kosovo
*Kosovo Vilayet, a former prefecture of the Ottoman Empire (1877–1912)

===Bulgaria===
*Kosovo, Kyustendil Province
*Kosovo, Plovdiv Province
*Kosovo, Shumen Province
*Kosovo, Vidin Province
*, a village in Suhindol Municipality, Veliko Tarnovo Province
*, a village in Byala Municipality, Ruse Province

===North Macedonia===
* Kosovo, Makedonski Brod, a village in the municipality of Makedonski Brod
* Kosovo Dabje, a village in the municipality of Delčevo

===Russia===

==Other uses==
*&quot;Kosovo&quot; (song), a song criticizing US involvement in the Kosovo War
*Malo Kosovo
*North Kosovo

==See also==
*Kosova (disambiguation)
*Kosovo Polje (disambiguation)
*Kosowo (disambiguation)
*Kosava (disambiguation)
*Kosów (disambiguation)
*Metohija (disambiguation)
*Names of Kosovo</text><links>
